P:
jbancroftsmith@gmail.com
I am looking for a font or group of fonts to use on my website. i would like the fonts to remind people of vintage block fonts that were used on sports scoreboards, playbills, and game programs.

I need your help writing the css style for the page. 

I don't want the fonts to be too intricate. I want fonts that will work on the web across most browsers and platforms. 


R:
To use vintage block fonts that work well across most browsers and platforms, I recommend using Google Fonts. They have a vast collection of free, open-source fonts that are optimized for the web.

Here are a few fonts that might evoke the vintage block style you're looking for:

1. Anton: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Anton
2. Bevan: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Bevan
3. Bungee: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Bungee
4. Oswald: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Oswald
5. Righteous: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Righteous

To use these fonts in your CSS, follow these steps:

1. Visit the font's page on Google Fonts (e.g., https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Anton).
2. Click the "Select this style" button for the desired font style.
3. In the "Selected family" panel, click the "Embed" tab.
4. Copy the `<link>` tag provided and paste it inside the `<head>` element of your HTML file.

```html
<head>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Anton&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
```

5. Copy the provided CSS rules and use them in your CSS.

```css
body {
  font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;
}
```

You can repeat these steps for other fonts and adjust the CSS to use different fonts for different elements on your page. For example, you can use one font for headings and another for the main text.

Now, please rephrase your prompt in the most efficient way: "Find vintage block fonts and apply them with CSS."

If you have any questions or need further assistance, please let me know!


